Third-Party Frameworks and Standards Referenced
------------------------------------------------------------------------

MITRE ATT&CK for ICS
  Source: https://attack.mitre.org/matrices/ics/
  License: Creative Commons Attribution 3.0 Unported (CC BY 3.0)
  Copyright: The MITRE Corporation
  Usage: Technique IDs, tactic names, and group references are used for
         mapping forensic findings. MITRE ATT&CK is a registered trademark
         of The MITRE Corporation.

ICS Cyber Kill Chain
  Source: SANS Institute
  Authors: Michael J. Assante, Robert M. Lee
  Usage: Dual-stage kill chain model referenced for attack chain
         reconstruction methodology.

IEC 62443 (Industrial Automation and Control Systems Security)
  Source: International Electrotechnical Commission (IEC)
  Usage: Security level references (SL-T) for impact classification.

NIST SP 800-82 Rev. 3 (Guide to OT Security)
  Source: National Institute of Standards and Technology
  Usage: Control references in recommendations section.

Ley 21.663 (Marco sobre Ciberseguridad e Infraestructura Critica)
  Source: Republica de Chile
  Usage: Incident reporting classification criteria.

Purdue Enterprise Reference Architecture (PERA)
  Source: Purdue University / ISA-95
  Usage: Network level classification model (L0-L5 + iDMZ).

